            <div type="l">
                <column>7</column>
                <head>Correspondence of the Spectator; The Weather--Politics and presumption--A
                    Rowdy Irishman--Negro Insurrection--Old Virginians--Sabbath Mail</head>
                <origin/>
                <commentary/>
                <excerpt/>
                <transcript/>
                <trailer>Yours, W. B. B.</trailer>
                <names/>
                <summary>Report from S.'s correspondant in Lexington, KY, describing life and
                    politics in that part of the country. Mentions concern over slaver insurrecton
                    insp. by Fremont's campaign. Praises Lexington for keeping the Sabbath, unklike
                    railroad in Staunton.</summary>
            </div>
