        </page>
        <page n="02" image="va.au.ss.1857.01.21.02">
            <div type="a">
                <column>2</column>
                <head>Prf. Schelo's Lecture</head>
                <origin/>
                <commentary/>
                <excerpt>The people of Staunton do not seem to appreciate such entertainments at
                    their proper value, and are more disposed to give thir money to strolling
                    minstrels and itinerant jugglers than they are to receive for half price the
                    solid and substantial entertainment afforded to people fo good taste by a
                    sensible lecture upon some interesting subject.</excerpt>
                <transcript/>
                <trailer/>
                <names>
                    <name>
                        <ln>Schelo</ln>
                        <fn>De Vere</fn>
                        <sf/>
                        <pf>Prof.</pf>
                    </name>
                </names>
                <summary>Prof. Schelo from UVA gave a lecture before the YMCA on 1/15 about the
                    Moravian Church. Spectator apologizes for poor turnout; complains about
                    Stauntonians' lack of interest in intellectual entertainments.</summary>
            </div>
            <div type="a">
                <column>2</column>
                <head>Daring Robbery</head>
                <origin/>
                <commentary/>
                <excerpt/>
                <transcript/>
                <trailer/>
                <names/>
                <summary>Two trunks stolen from AMerican Hotel on 1/14; later recovered, one under
                    Railroad Bridge, other on Abney's Hill. Theives have not been caught</summary>
            </div>
            <div type="a">
                <column>2</column>
                <head>Terrible Snow Storm</head>
