            <div type="l">
                <column>3</column>
                <head>For the Spectator; To the Citizens of Deerfield and Vicinity</head>
                <origin/>
                <commentary/>
                <excerpt>By our late change (so liberally tendered by the P. M. G.) in the Mail
                    Route to this place, we hope to have no more delays; and that it will not take a
                    paper from March to January to reach you as has been the case.</excerpt>
                <transcript/>
                <trailer>Yours, P. M.; Deerfield, January 21, 1857</trailer>
                <names/>
                <summary>Describes changes in postal service.</summary>
            </div>
